We've changed allegiances. This is now our preferred Starbucks.  New! Clean! Open and airy and filled with light woods and a good sound system. We leave after spending some hours here once or twice a weekend with much less eau d' Starbucks permeating our clothing.  Employees come and go at these places, as you know. This location's core staff is terrific, with a special nod and doff of the hat to Bailey, a particularly charming, friendly and efficient person who never fails to share and elicit a smile. S. and I really do appreciate Bailey and coffee on a weekend morning. Everyone here has  behaved  in an exemplary fashion within all our interactions and in all our observations.  All told then,  go out of your way if necessary and enjoy this Starbucks. ~Peter and S. O.
